  "translations": {
    "en": "«So for God, for the Messenger, and for those with close kinship, the orphans, the poor, and the wayfarer» — specifically about us — «so that it does not become rotating wealth among the wealthy among you. What the Messenger brought you, take it; and what he forbade you from, abstain from it. And fear God regarding wronging the family of Muhammad. Indeed, God is severe in punishment for those who wrong them» — as a mercy from Him for us and wealth/sufficiency with which God has made us self-sufficient.",
